[According to information received from a reliable source, and as stated and shown by the Kazakh TV (a video clip may be shared through whatsapp upon request), the animals reportedly manifested drooling during 1-2 days prior to death.

Acute death in cattle of all ages may be caused by infectious and non-infectious (e.g., toxicological) agents; it may also have an iatrogenic etiology. Gross pathological changes are of particular interest to exclude rinderpest (not likely, in the absence of diarrhea); lab and epidemiological investigation results are anticipated with interest.

Koktal, a village, in the East Kazakhstan region, is situated about 58 km [36 mi] distant from China's border to its east (map at https://tinyurl.com/y7oc8f6l. - Mod.AS]
